Adult male.description: Hermit Warblers have an unmarked yellow face and a white breast without the dark cheek patch and yellow breast of Townsend's Warbler.

Female/immature.description: Hermit Warblers have an unmarked yellow face and a white breast. They lack the dark cheek patch and yellow breast of Townsend's Warbler.

Male.description: Golden-cheeked Warblers have a thinner black eyeline and white underparts unlike Townsend's Warbler. The two species' breeding ranges do not overlap.

Female.description: Golden-cheeked Warblers have a thinner black eyeline and white underparts unlike Townsend's Warbler. The two species' breeding ranges do not overlap.

Adult male.description: Black-throated Green Warblers have less black on the face and an olive, not black, crown. Ranges do not overlap.

Adult female.description: Female Black-throated Green Warblers have a white (not yellow) breast. Ranges do not overlap.
